  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2003-05-08",
    "date": "2006-11-28T17:35:40Z",
    "text": "Amends the Federal judicial code to include a chief judge of a district as a \"judicial official\" who may provide for survivor annuities. Allows six months for an individual who became such a chief judge between January 1, 2002, and the date of this Act's enactment, but who has not filed a written notification of his or her intention to provide for survivor annuities, to file such notification."
